ssh-copy-id -f "-o IdentityFile <PATH TO PEM FILE>" ubuntu@<INSTANCE-PUBLIC-IP>

sudo cat ~/.ssh/id_ed25519.pub | ssh -i key ubuntu@13.203.200.132 "mkdir -p ~/.ssh && chmod 700 
~/.ssh && cat >> ~/.ssh/authorized_keys && chmod 600 ~/.ssh/authorized_keys"





Option 3: Use Ad-hoc Ansible Command (Quick Test)
If you just want to run a script quickly without writing a playbook:


ansible server1 -m script -a "./files/myscript.sh"
Script already on remote server:

ansible server1 -a "/path/to/script.sh"
